Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a Bayesian nonparametric approach to learn interaction patterns between the ego vehicle and other nearby vehicles. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on autonomous vehicles and their interactions with other vehicles in lane change scenarios. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper uses data from real-world settings to evaluate the proposed approach, which may involve computer vision techniques for data processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning approach to learn interaction patterns in multi-agent scenarios. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the development of an acceleration-sensitive velocity field based on Gaussian processes, which may involve control theory concepts.
